  "text": "The results of [CITATION_1] show that for batched binary-field arithmetic on the Intel Core 2 processor bitsliced implementations are faster than non-bitsliced implementations. However, the question whether this is also the case on the SPU of the Cell processor is hard to answer a priori for several reasons:",
